    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>curry powder</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>on a plate</p><p>Add your <strong>hake fillet[s] </strong>and cover until they're completely coated</p><p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated hake</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through – this is your<strong> curried hake</strong></p>",
